dir="auto"><h1 tabindex="-1" class="heading-element" dir="auto">Introduction</h1><a id="user-content-introduction" class="anchor" aria-label="Permalink: Introduction" href="#introduction"><svg 0l-2.5 2.5a1.998 1.998 0 0 0 0 2.83Z"></path></svg></a></div>
<p dir="auto">I noticed that ePub files with DRM protection sometimes contain an invalid filename field for one or more entries.
In these cases the decrypting tool INEPT gives error when it tries to decode the string of the filename.</p>
<p dir="auto"><a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" href="https://github.com/marcocod/epub-repair-tool/blob/master/img/inept.png?raw=true"><img src="https://github.com/marcocod/epub-repair-tool/raw/master/img/inept.png?raw=true" alt="alt text" style="max-width: 100%;"></a></p>
<p dir="auto">If you open the ePub file with a archive manager program as 7zip you can see that some filenames contain invalid characters.</p>
<p dir="auto"><a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" href="https://github.com/marcocod/epub-repair-tool/blob/master/img/7zip.png?raw=true"><img src="https://github.com/marcocod/epub-repair-tool/raw/master/img/7zip.png?raw=true" alt="alt text" style="max-width: 100%;"></a></p>
<p dir="auto">Note that since the filename contains the entire relative path, archive manager programs can show the corrupted entry in the wrong subdirectory.</p>
<div class="markdown-heading" dir="auto"><h1 tabindex="-1" class="heading-element" dir="auto">ePub format</h1><a id="user-content-epub-format" class="anchor" aria-label="Permalink: ePub format" href="#epub-format"><svg class="octicon octicon-link" viewBox="0 0 16 16" version="1.1" width="16" height="16" aria-hidden="true"><path d="m7.775 3.275 1.25-1.25a3.5 3.5 0 1 1 4.95 4.95l-2.5 2.5a3.5 3.5 0 0 1-4.95 0 .751.751 0 0 1 .018-1.042.751.751 0 0 1 1.042-.018 1.998 1.998 0 0 0 2.83 0l2.5-2.5a2.002 2.002 0 0 0-2.83-2.83l-1.25 1.25a.751.751 0 0 1-1.042-.018.751.751 0 0 1-.018-1.042Zm-4.69 9.64a1.998 1.998 0 0 0 2.83 0l1.25-1.25a.751.751 0 0 1 1.042.018.751.751 0 0 1 .018 1.042l-1.25 1.25a3.5 3.5 0 1 1-4.95-4.95l2.5-2.5a3.5 3.5 0 0 1 4.95 0 .751.751 0 0 1-.018 1.042.751.751 0 0 1-1.042.018 1.998 1.998 0 0 0-2.83 0l-2.5 2.5a1.998 1.998 0 0 0 0 2.83Z"></path></svg></a></div>
<p dir="auto">The ePub file is a zip archive and in this format the information of each entry is contained in two different headers:</p>
<ul dir="auto">
<li>Local File Header (LFH)</li>
<li>Central Directory File Header (CDFH)</li>
</ul>
<p dir="auto">Usually the filename field in both these headers (CDFH and LFH) should be equal, but sometimes ePub with DRM protection contains few entries where the filename in the CDFH is corrupted and differs from the correct filename contained in the LFH.</p>
<div class="markdown-heading" dir="auto"><h1 tabindex="-1" class="heading-element" dir="auto">How the tool works</h1><a id="user-content-how-the-tool-works" class="anchor" aria-label="Permalink: How the tool works" href="#how-the-tool-works"><svg class="octicon octicon-link" viewBox="0 0 16 16" version="1.1" width="16" height="16" aria-hidden="true"><path d="m7.775 3.275 1.25-1.25a3.5 3.5 0 1 1 4.95 4.95l-2.5 2.5a3.5 3.5 0 0 1-4.95 0 .751.751 0 0 1 .018-1.042.751.751 0 0 1 1.042-.018 1.998 1.998 0 0 0 2.83 0l2.5-2.5a2.002 2.002 0 0 0-2.83-2.83l-1.25 1.25a.751.751 0 0 1-1.042-.018.751.751 0 0 1-.018-1.042Zm-4.69 9.64a1.998 1.998 0 0 0 2.83 0l1.25-1.25a.751.751 0 0 1 1.042.018.751.751 0 0 1 .018 1.042l-1.25 1.25a3.5 3.5 0 1 1-4.95-4.95l2.5-2.5a3.5 3.5 0 0 1 4.95 0 .751.751 0 0 1-.018 1.042.751.751 0 0 1-1.042.018 1.998 1.998 0 0 0-2.83 0l-2.5 2.5a1.998 1.998 0 0 0 0 2.83Z"></path></svg></a></div>
<p dir="auto">ePub repair tool analyzes the ePub files contained in the selected folder and detects the files with entries where filename fields of LFH and CDFH are not consistent.
These files are shown in the list on the left (files in read only mode will be skipped).</p>
<p dir="auto"><a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" href="https://github.com/marcocod/epub-repair-tool/blob/master/img/jar.png?raw=true"><img src="https://github.com/marcocod/epub-repair-tool/raw/master/img/jar.png?raw=true" alt="alt text" style="max-width: 100%;"></a></p>
<p dir="auto">For each file you can check in the table on the right the invalid entries detected by the tool.</p>
<p dir="auto">Clicking on button "Repair files" the program overwrites the invalid filename field of CDFH with the correct filename field of LFH.
Note that this tool doesn't create any backup file.</p>
<div class="markdown-heading" dir="auto"><h1 tabindex="-1" class="heading-element" dir="auto">How to build</h1><a id="user-content-how-to-build" class="anchor" aria-label="Permalink: How to build" href="#how-to-build"><svg class="octicon octicon-link" viewBox="0 0 16 16" version="1.1" width="16" height="16" aria-hidden="true"><path d="m7.775 3.275 1.25-1.25a3.5 3.5 0 1 1 4.95 4.95l-2.5 2.5a3.5 3.5 0 0 1-4.95 0 .751.751 0 0 1 .018-1.042.751.751 0 0 1 1.042-.018 1.998 1.998 0 0 0 2.83 0l2.5-2.5a2.002 2.002 0 0 0-2.83-2.83l-1.25 1.25a.751.751 0 0 1-1.042-.018.751.751 0 0 1-.018-1.042Zm-4.69 9.64a1.998 1.998 0 0 0 2.83 0l1.25-1.25a.751.751 0 0 1 1.042.018.751.751 0 0 1 .018 1.042l-1.25 1.25a3.5 3.5 0 1 1-4.95-4.95l2.5-2.5a3.5 3.5 0 0 1 4.95 0 .751.751 0 0 1-.018 1.042.751.751 0 0 1-1.042.018 1.998 1.998 0 0 0-2.83 0l-2.5 2.5a1.998 1.998 0 0 0 0 2.83Z"></path></svg></a></div>
<p dir="auto">The repository contains:</p>
<ul dir="auto">
<li>the java source code in the src folder</li>
<li>the NetBeans project files in the nbproject folder</li>
</ul>
<p dir="auto">The code can be built with NetBeans version 8.2 or above opening the repository folder as project folder.
The build requires a Java Development Kit (JDK) version 8 or above.</p>
<div class="markdown-heading" dir="auto"><h1 tabindex="-1" class="heading-element" dir="auto">How to launch</h1><a id="user-content-how-to-launch" class="anchor" aria-label="Permalink: How to launch" href="#how-to-launch"><svg class="octicon octicon-link" viewBox="0 0 16 16" version="1.1" width="16" height="16" aria-hidden="true"><path d="m7.775 3.275 1.25-1.25a3.5 3.5 0 1 1 4.95 4.95l-2.5 2.5a3.5 3.5 0 0 1-4.95 0 .751.751 0 0 1 .018-1.042.751.751 0 0 1 1.042-.018 1.998 1.998 0 0 0 2.83 0l2.5-2.5a2.002 2.002 0 0 0-2.83-2.83l-1.25 1.25a.751.751 0 0 1-1.042-.018.751.751 0 0 1-.018-1.042Zm-4.69 9.64a1.998 1.998 0 0 0 2.83 0l1.25-1.25a.751.751 0 0 1 1.042.018.751.751 0 0 1 .018 1.042l-1.25 1.25a3.5 3.5 0 1 1-4.95-4.95l2.5-2.5a3.5 3.5 0 0 1 4.95 0 .751.751 0 0 1-.018 1.042.751.751 0 0 1-1.042.018 1.998 1.998 0 0 0-2.83 0l-2.5 2.5a1.998 1.998 0 0 0 0 2.83Z"></path></svg></a></div>
<p dir="auto">The release is a Java Archive (JAR) that can be executed with a Java Runtime Environment (JRE) version 8 or above with the following command:</p>
<p dir="auto">java -jar epub-repair-tool.jar</p>
